Base layer is colemak, uses the two layer switch keys to access upper and lower. While in upper or lower press space to go even deeper.


Purpose of each layer

Base:
Colemak layer used for typing

Lower:

Symbols

Lower2:





Raise:

Number row plus directional navigation. May add mousenav



Raise2:





Lower + Raise:
Workspace navigation




Gaming is a toggle base, replaces colemak with a layer designed for gaming. Has a key to go back to colemak. As of now has no layers on top.



